      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BETTER CALL (7) has some solid form under his belt and proved too classy last time to win by a nose at Q Straight in a handy 19.15 beating Electric Man. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from five starts. Well placed and will be tough to beat. SCOUT BOBBER (2) has been hard to follow lately, running seventh (19.38) last time but prior to that ran very well when placed at Q Straight. Can improve sharply here. NANA MARIE (4) turned in a solid run last start over 366m at this track finishing 5th and beaten only 4 lengths (20.15). Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw. Has the ability to give this a shake. PIERRE HAYZE (3) is always a threat when he races at this track and distance.",
